# Marketing copy

See also: **`pages/page-layout.mdc`**, **`ui/interaction-polish.mdc`** (no eyebrow spam).  
In-app settings, forms, tables → **`ui-microcopy.mdc`**.  
Audit: [`.cursor/skills/ai-slop-check/`](../../skills/ai-slop-check/SKILL.md) (`catalog.md` § Copy — marketing). Index: [`skills/SKILL.md`](../../skills/SKILL.md).

**Purpose:** Landing and marketing strings may be more expressive than product UI — but still **specific**, not generic AI SaaS voice.

## Headlines & sections

- **Headline:** short claim or outcome — not a long sentence at display size (`slop-oversized-hero-headline`).
- **Subhead:** one concrete benefit or how it works — not a second headline.
- Drop **section kickers** (`INTRODUCING`, `WHY US`) unless the design system requires them (`slop-section-kicker`, `slop-hero-eyebrow`).
- Avoid **aphorism cadence** repeated every section: “Not spreadsheets. Insights.” → explain plainly (`slop-aphorism`).

## Body copy

- Prefer **concrete nouns and verbs** over abstractions.
- **Em dashes:** max **2 per screen** of body copy; prefer commas or periods (`slop-em-dash`).
- No **buzzword clusters**: streamline, empower, supercharge, world-class, enterprise-grade, seamless, leverage (`slop-buzzword`, `slop-hype-verb`).
- No **theater framing** (“growth theater”, performative dismissals) — say what the product does (`slop-theater`).

## CTAs

Same specificity as product UI, but tone can be slightly bolder:

```tsx
// Bad
<Button>Get started</Button>
<Button>Learn more</Button>

// Good — names the action or destination
<Button>Start free trial</Button>
<Button>See pricing</Button>
```

Secondary CTAs must differ in **intent**, not duplicate “Learn more” three times on one page.

## Social proof & metrics

- Only show **real** numbers and logos (`slop-hero-metrics`).
- No fabricated “10,000+ teams trust us” without a source.

## Feature grids

Identical icon + title + blurb cards are a layout smell — vary copy length and structure when you can’t vary layout yet (`slop-identical-card-grid`). Each blurb: **one capability + one outcome**, not three adjectives.

## Handoff to product UI

Marketing promises must match in-app language. If the hero says “Instant exports”, the button inside should say `Export CSV`, not `Unlock powerful exports`.

## Audit

For landing-page reviews, run **`@ai-slop-check`** on the route — it covers visual slop and copy IDs together.
